summary: Bill Fanter provides comprehensive weekly watchlist for October 6th week, emphasizing caution due to government shutdown preventing release of critical jobs data needed for Fed rate decisions. He analyzes major tech stocks (SPY, QQQ, AAPL, AMZN, MSFT, GOOGL, TSLA, NVDA, AMD, PLTR, META, NFLX) with specific price levels for entries, noting bearish pressure on Friday but identifying key demand zones for potential long setups. Heavy emphasis on patience, waiting for price to come to specific levels rather than chasing, and being aware of upcoming Fed speakers and FOMC meeting minutes.
